<directions xmlns:php="http://php.net/xsl">&gt;
<step><![CDATA[for acid butter: take butter out of friedge a couple of ours before hand
cut onions in small chunks, and reduce in the liquids at very low fire until halved
discard onion, mix 2 tsp of mixture into butter until creamy]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[
stock: put ingrendients in pot, bring to boil, the salt lightly and simmer at very low temperature until tasty]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[
hard boil eggs, then sieve yolks to create a dust. Use whites for another dish]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[cook the asparagus 5-10 mins in the stock (if feasible), or water, then take out and chill]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[
cut tip off asparagus and put aside, and puré stalks into a cream]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[
prepare risotto as per normal: on high fire sauté onion in butter, stir in rice, add wine and when evaporated add asparagus cream, then ladle in warm stock bit by bit. Salt when almost ready.]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[
fluff up with butter (or acid butter if using) and parmesan, add asparagus tips and leave covered a couple of mins away from fire]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[
serve with the egg yolks]]></step>
</directions>
